bject matter of ch. 61 is closely re-</div><div class="t macd x21 h4 y82 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lated to that of ch. 60 (compare ch. 61:3 </div><div class="t m4aa x21 h4 y85 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with ch. 60:9, 15, 18, 20, 21). </div><div class="t made x4b h4 y5e8 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Ancient Jewish expositors recognized </div><div class="t m3d7 x21 h4 y4a0 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Messianic import of this and many </div><div class="t m2b5 x21 h4 y87 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">other passages in Isaiah. Verses 1-3 pre-</div><div class="t mce5 x21 h4 y1218 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sent a graphic picture of what the Messiah </div><div class="t m2d8 x1f h4 y1219 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[34</div><div class="t m247b xbc hb y1219 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 </div><div class="t m14df xb0 hb y12c4 ff2 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
